reviewText: I was impressed that this was much different than expected.  The storyline made me laugh.  Each story about each person was QUITE interesting and I found myself cheering on the underdog. Very pleased and would watch it again.

reviewText: This is a complete gem of a film - funny dialogue, adorable characters, quoteable moments, with a sweetness that runs through the whole thing. This is one of those films I'm glad to own...it never disappoints. Bad day + The Night We Never Met = Much, much better day. Be sure to set yourself up by getting some good cheese and wine and a couple other gourmet snacks before watching - seeing Matthew Broderick at the cheese counter in Dean and Deluca will make you crave something exquisite.
